						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in the ruined Vishṇu Temple situated to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>13th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription, the date portion of which is lost, may be assigned to 13th century A.D. on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Begining portion of the epigraph is broken and lost. It seems to record a gift of a plate <hi rend="italic">(paḷḷeraṁ)</hi> by a certain Garuḍa-dāsi.</p>						

						</summary>
